The MIDFLORIDA Credit Union Amphitheatre is an outdoor entertainment facility in Tampa, FL located on the Florida State Fairgrounds, adjacent to Interstate 4, in the eastern side of town. With a capacity of approximately 20,000, it is the largest outdoor concert-only facility in the Tampa Bay Area providing the best outdoor entertainment experience.

Since 2004, the amphitheater has played host to over 300 major concerts and festivals including superstar artists such as Jimmy Buffett, Bruce Springsteen, Dave Matthews Band, Kenny Chesney, Aerosmith, Sting and Big Guava Music Festival.

